istory-over-2013-cba-agreement_c1468033|title=Doctors begin 'longest strike in history' over 2013 CBA agreement|last=Mwangi|first=William|date=2016-12-05|newspaper=The Star|language=en-US|access-date=2016-03-14}}</ref> *2017 [[Vandenberg Air Force Base]] civilian workers<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.keyt.com/news/civilian-contract-workers-strike-at-vafb/317440881|title=Civilian Contract Workers Strike at VAFB|access-date=2017-02-10}}</ref> *2017 Palestinian General Strike in support of political prisoners hunger strike<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maannews.com/Content.aspx?id=777210|title=Palestinians observe general strike in solidarity with hunger-striking prisoners|access-date=2017-10-10}}</ref> * 2017: [[2017 Catalan general strike|3rd October Catalan independentists General Strike]] * 2017: 8 November Catalan independentists General Strike<ref>[http://www.dailymail.co.uk/wires/ap/article-5061269/Striking-protesters-disrupt-transportation-Catalonia.html Catalonia strike is muted but protesters block roads, trains]</ref> * 2018: [[2018 West Virginia teachers' strike]], begun on February 22 * 2018 University Lecturer Strike<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ucu.org.uk/strikeforuss|access-date=2018-02-27}}</ref> * 2018 [[2018 York University strike]]: Teaching Assistants, Graduate Assistant, Research Assistant, and Contract Faculty Strike * 2018: [[Arizona]] teacher strike * 2018: Brazil [[truck driver]]s' strike * 2018: [[SNCF]] train transport strike in France<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-43617033|title=Rail chaos in three-month French strike|date=2018-04-03|work=BBC News|access-date=2018-06-02|language=en-GB}}</ref> * 2018: [[Vermont]] nurses' strike<ref>https://www.jacobinmag.com/2018/07/vermont-nurses-strike-safe-staffing-ratios</ref><ref>https://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/news/2018/07/16/nurses-strikes-nurses-feeling-overworked-across-country/783587002/</ref> * 2018: Iran [[truck driver]]s' strike * 2018: [[Rhode Island]] 