{{Infobox award | name = Sultan Qaboos Prize for Environmental Preservation | current_awards = | image = | imagesize = | caption = [[UNESCO]] Headquarters in [[Paris]] | description = outstanding contributions by individuals, groups of individuals, institutes or organizations in the management or preservation of the environment | presenter = [[UNESCO]] and Sultan [[Qaboos Bin Said]] of [[Oman]] | country = | location = | year = 1991 | website = http://www.unesco.org/mab/prizes/sq.shtml }}
The '''Sultan Qaboos Prize for Environmental Preservation''' is a biennial award sponsored by the [[United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization]] (UNESCO) and the Sultan [[Qaboos Bin Said]] of [[Oman]] "to afford recognition to outstanding contributions by individuals, groups of individuals, institutes or organizations in the management or preservation of the environment, consistent with the policies, aims and objectives of UNESCO, and in relation to the Organization's programmes in this field."<ref name = "unesco"> {{citeweb |author = UNESCO | title = Sultan Qaboos Prize for Environmental Preservation | url = http://www.unesco.org/mab/prizes/sq.shtml | accessdate = 2008-06-02 }}</ref>
The award consists of a diploma and a grant of [[USD]] $70,000.00, which is financed by the interest on a [[USD]] $250,000.00 donation by Sultan Qaboos Bin Said.<ref> {{citeweb| author = UNESCO | title = Report by the Director-General on the Overall Review of UNESCO Prizes | url = http://unesdoc.unesco.org/images/0013/001385/138524e.pdf | format = pdf | accessdate = 2008-06-02 }}</ref>
==Laureates== Source: [http://www.unesco.org/new/en/natural-sciences/environment/ecological-sciences/man-and-biosphere-programme/awards-and-prizes/sultan-qaboos/winners/ UNESCO] * '''1991''': Instituto de Ecología, A.C. ({{MEX}}). * '''1993''': [[Jan Jenik]] ({{CZE}}). * '''1995''': [[Lake Malawi National Park]] ({{MWI}}). * '''1997''': Department of Environmental Sciences, [[Alexandria University]] ({{EGY}}) and Forest Department ({{LKA}}). * '''1999''': [[Charles Darwin Foundation]] ({{ECU}}) * '''2001''': Chad Association of Volunteers for the Protection of the Environment ({{TCD}}). * '''2003''': Center for Ecology ({{flag|Venezuela|1930}}) and [[Peter Schei|Peter Johan Schei]] ({{NOR}}). * '''2005''': [[Great Barrier Reef Marine Park Authority]] ({{AUS}}) and [[Ernesto Enkerlin]] ({{MEX}}). * '''2007''': Institute of Biodiversity Conservation ({{flag|Ethiopia|1996}}) and [[Julius Oszlányi]] ({{SVK}}). * '''2009''': Autonomous Authority for National Parks (OAPN) ({{ESP}}). * '''2011''': Institute for Forest Research of [[Nigeria]] * '''2013''': [[State Forests (Poland)|State Forests National Forest Holding]] of [[Poland]] ({{POL}}) and South Africa’s Endangered Wildlife Trust ({{RSA}}) * '''2015''': Fabio A. Kalesnik, Horacio Sirolli and Luciano Iribarren of the Wetlands Ecology Research Group of the [[University of Buenos Aires]], Argentina ({{ARG}})
==External links== *[http://www.unesco.org/new/en/natural-sciences/environment/ecological-sciences/man-and-biosphere-programme/awards-and-prizes/sultan-qaboos/ UNESCO: Sultan Qaboos Prize for Environmental Preservation]
